<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Kreismann</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-09-13"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 13, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of August 22 (No. 12) has
                            been received. The leading features of the project of reform, as laid
                            before the congress of German princes which lately assembled at
                            Frankfort, by the Emperor of Austria, are stated by you with great
                            clearness, and your reflections upon the subject, as well as upon other
                            questions which at present engage the attention of the German states,
                            are interesting and instructive.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Hermann Kreismann</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Berlin.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>